https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/find-the-smallest-and-second-smallest-element-in-an-array3226/1?page=5&category=Arrays&sortBy=submissions

Given an array, arr[] of integers, your task is to return the smallest and second smallest element in the array. If the smallest and second smallest do not exist, return -1.

class Solution {
    public ArrayList<Integer> minAnd2ndMin(int[] arr) {
        ArrayList<Integer> res = new ArrayList<>();
        int n = arr.length;

        if (n < 2) {
            res.add(-1);
            return res;
        }

        Arrays.sort(arr);

        int min = arr[0];
        int secondMin = -1;

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            if (arr[i] > min) {
                secondMin = arr[i];
                break;
            }
        }

        if (secondMin == -1) {
            res.add(-1);
        } else {
            res.add(min);
            res.add(secondMin);
        }

        return res;
    }
}
